2. Albarino CG, Palacios G, Khristova ML, et al. High Diversity and Ancient Common Ancestry of Lymphocytic Choriomeningitis Virus. Emerging Infectious Diseases. 2010;16(7):1093-1100. doi: https://doi.org.10.3201/eid1607.091902.

3. Prevention, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), Lymphocytic choriomeningitis (LCM) factsheet. Accessed 4th August, 2021. https://www.cdc.gov/vhf/lcm/index.html

4. McCutcheon J. Farmer 'lucky to be alive' after contracting deadly rodent-borne disease during mouse plague. ABC News, 2021. Accessed 5th August, 2021. https://www.abc.net.au/news/2021-04-04/mouse-plague-farmer-contracts-lymphocytic-choriomeningitis/100037256

